President Joseph R. Biden, Jr. has declared a major disaster in Kentucky due to severe storms, straight-line winds, flooding, landslides, and mudslides that occurred from February 15 to February 20, 2023. This declaration allows for federal aid to supplement recovery efforts in the affected areas. Federal funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Myra M. Shird of FEMA has been appointed to coordinate federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Further designations may be made based on damage assessments. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk at (202) 646-3272 or FEMA-NEWS-DESK@FEMA.DHS.GOV.